what's the difference between import "name" from "module" and import * as "name" from "module"?

First let's just understand how imports works so consider i have a file with the following exports // file name -> modules export const add = (x, y) => x + y; (2 more lines were trimmed) now i can import all these functions on another file like this import defaultFunction, { add, subtract } from './modules.js';
(3 more lines were trimmed) or i can use import * as from to import all the exports inside a file. like this import * as myModules from './modules.js'; // NOTE: this will only give you add and subtract functions but not the default one (14 more lines were trimmed) Conclusion I think the problem is that the library that you're using is not providing a default export to actually use import expressBasicAuth from 'express-basic-auth'; or it might be exporting different functions for named exports and default exports
